Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph chapter set-title

chapter set-title

Purpose:
  Rename an existing chapter in the archive TOC.

Usage:
  wikigraph chapter set-title <path> --chapter <id> --title <title> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph chapter set-title <path> --chapter <id> --clear [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]

Behavior:
  - Updates only the chapter title stored in the TOC.
  - Does not change source text, graph nodes, summaries, or metadata.
  - `--title <title>` sets the explicit title.
  - `--clear` removes the explicit title and shows `[untitled]`.
  - `--title` and `--clear` are mutually exclusive.
  - Does not call an LLM provider.

Output shape:
  Prints the updated chapter status.

Examples:
  wikigraph chapter set-title book.sdpub --chapter 12 --title "New Chapter Title"
  wikigraph chapter set-title book.sdpub --chapter 12 --clear

See also:
  - wikigraph chapter list --help
  - wikigraph chapter status --help
  - wikigraph help command
